Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
analyze_package(25.10)                                  analyze_package(25.10)

Name
       analyze_package

Syntax
       analyze_package

       [-help] <<domain>>

       [-computer_resources <string>]

       [-output <<directoryname>>]

       -pkg_bga_name <<bga_circuitname>>

       -pkg_die_name <<die_circuitname>>

       -pkg_pin_current_file <<filename>>

       -result_name <<filename>>

       [-spd_file <filename>]

       -type <<package_analysis_type>>

       -workspace <<workspace_name>>

       Specifies  how the package analysis will be performed, and to run pack-
       age analysis.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs the command usage and a brief description about the com-
              mand parameters.

       <domain>
              Specifies the rail analysis domain name.

       -computer_resources <string>
              Specifies the computer resources for the package  analysis  run.
              This parameter allows you to customize the host distribution/CPU
              usage  for package analysis. The default setting is "-smt 0 -lo-
              cal -cn localhost -cpus 8".

       -output <<directoryname>>
              Specifies the output directory name of the package analysis  re-
              sults.  By  default,  the  package  model will be created in the
              specified workspace.

       -pkg_bga_name <<bga_circuitname>>
              Defines the ball grid array (BGA) circuit name  in  the  package
              model.

       -pkg_die_name <<die_circuitname>>
              Defines the die circuit name in the package model.

       -pkg_pin_current_file <<filename>>
              Specifies  the  name of the generated pin current file from rail
              analysis that contains the package pin  names  and  the  current
              values. It is automatically generated after the package model is
              created.

       -result_name <<filename>>
              Specifies the name of the .xml result file.

       -spd_file <filename>
              Specifies  an  existing  Sigrity .spd file for package analysis.
              This parameter allows you to specify a .spd file instead of  the
              workspace  name (package model database) of the package analysis
              (PowerDC) tool.

       -type <<package_analysis_type>>
              Specifies the type of package analysis. Currently, the  software
              supports only DC package analysis.

       -workspace <<workspace_name>>
              Specifies the workspace name for package analysis (powerDC). The
              file name extension is .pdcx.

Example
              * The  following  example specifies the package analysis details
                and starts package analysis:

                analyze_package ALL \

                -type dc \

                -workspace /../sigrity/rak_pdc_irdrop/test.pdcx \

                -pkg_bga_name FPBGA144_Signal02 \

                -pkg_die_name CD1_Signal01 \

                -output rak_pdc_irdrop_voltus_cpf \

                -result_name rak_pdc_irdrop_voltus \

                -pkg_pin_current_file   /../spa_cpf/ALL_125C_avg_1/Reports/su-
                per_filter_pkg_iv.rpt

